@page "/"

<PageTitle>Contoso Bank — Product demo</PageTitle>

<h1>Contoso Bank back-office</h1>

<p>
    This product UI demonstrates one fintech workflow travelling through four
    authorization layers, each with a visible outcome:
</p>

<ol class="layers">
    <li><strong>AuthN</strong> — Keycloak OIDC sign-in issues an access token carrying
        your roles, tenant, and scopes.</li>
    <li><strong>Coarse gateway</strong> — the edge gateway checks token + scope + tenant
        before routing to the domain API.</li>
    <li><strong>Fine PDP</strong> — Bank.Api enforces maker-checker, segregation of
        duties, and tenant scoping on each resource.</li>
    <li><strong>Entitlements</strong> — commercial plan / feature gates decide what the
        tenant is licensed to do.</li>
</ol>

<AuthorizeView>
    <Authorized>
        <p class="notice">
            Signed in as <strong>@context.User.Identity?.Name</strong>.
            Explore <a href="accounts">Accounts</a> to see the read path end to end, or
            <a href="claims">your claims</a>.
        </p>
        <p><a class="button" href="logout">Log out</a></p>
    </Authorized>
    <NotAuthorized>
        <p class="notice">You are not signed in.</p>
        <p><a class="button" href="login">Log in</a></p>
    </NotAuthorized>
</AuthorizeView>

<h2>Explore</h2>
<ul>
    <li><a href="accounts">Accounts</a> — read vertical slice (AuthN → coarse → read).</li>
    <li><a href="transactions/new">New Transaction</a> — maker create flow.</li>
